rComments: A good prof. Assignments and exam were all fair. I found the class content itself to be pretty dry but he does well in making it interesting and includes information from his own experiences. Not the most captivating ever but he's good overall.

Prof Peker was an absolute sweetheart. You can tell by his lectures that he is passionate about this subject. I did not like to topic and would not take it again but listening to his lectures was very interesting for me. His exams are fair and assignments as well. He goes through his expectations for both very clearly in class.

was a good prof. You can tell he's knowledgeable in his field. He'd tell stories and make connections to the content we were learning in the current news. textbook is necessary if you want to do well on the midterm and final. he went over our assignments and would provide an example or template, and answer any questions we had about the assignments

He's a really nice guy and I good prof. He's young but is able to hold the class's attention really well because his lectures are super interesting. He's in constant contact with his TA's and grading is consistent between markers. The class itself was very interesting and he taught the material in a very effective and fun way.

Prof. Peker was the highlight of my first semester! Hes funny, engaging and clearly passionate about sociology. Learned a lot about race & ethnicity and loved the GIFs! Id take whatever course hes teaching.

Professor Peker was a boring, unfunny, and arrogant lecturer, his high rating boggles my mind. His attitude was always condescending and took 25-40 minutes to start the content of the lecture, just talking about irrelevant topics at the start. However, the class itself was extremely easy and felt like a high school class, easy A if you put in work.
The grade standard is not fair.

I really appreciated my semester with prof peker. He makes his classes very interactive even if the subject was dry. He can be a little slow in his explanations making us rush the end, but other than that, he is great!

Prof. Peker is a fair teacher. He has reasonable expectations and provides many resources to help students succeed. Study material involves just the textbook and the weekly powerpoints, which are both straightforward. The few assignments in the class are worth a lot of marks, but they aren't difficult, just lots of writing. Also, he's hilarious!

One of the nicest profs I've ever had. You can tell he likes the content that he teaches and wants his students to enjoy it as well. We would have one mini assignment every week that actually helped me understand the content much more. Only one paper and two exams, so not bad if you hate big assignments/tests. I would love to take his class again!

My favorite prof by far! Made lectures super engaging and fun, was extremely accommodating to online situation and made a real effort to lighten the course load. He's funny and kind, super accessible and approachable, and made the class so much more enjoyable. Textbook and keeping up with readings is super important as all exams are based on it.

Took this class right before the pandemic hit and he is one of the best professors I've had. Clear, straight forward. TA's were fair graders. Make sure to go over your textbook and the ppt notes because the exams + midterm are the exact same.

Amazing prof, found the exam difficult but I definitely did not study enough. Took as an elective, would recommend for sure. Textbook is extremely important in my opinion. Amazing lecturer and great stories that were great additions to content. Hilarious guy but extremely respected. A couple assignments but not hard at all, start early.

Exams are relatively easy, based mostly on definitions. Multiple choice. I personally didn't find his class engaging and found his teaching boring but I suppose its different for everyone! Two multiple choice exams and like 2 essays.
Professor Parker is the best of the best. This was a 1st year class but it was a breeze. Show up to class, engage, and you'll get an A. Can't praise this guy enough
This prof is great. He is very kind. He makes a boring class like methodology not so bad. His exams are pretty easy, make sure to study the resumes of the chapters and A+
teacherRatingTags: ['Clear grading criteria', 'Gives good feedback', 'Accessible outside class']

rComments: Probably wont find a kinder prof. Really understanding, caring and easy going prof. Gave us 5 free questions for both the midterm and final which were both multiple choice, assignments were easy and straightforward and class content obviously relates to everyday life so its pretty simple. Easy A.

Prof. Peker is truly one of the best profs you can have at this university. He's a great teacher and his assignments are extremely fair. Also, was excellent at managing online learning. If you ever have the opportunity to take a class with Prof. Peker, I highly recommend.
This professor runs his own academic meme page. If that doesn't convince you that he's an utter gem at this university then I don't know what will. Best prof out of all my first semester courses.

hands down best prof ever. everyone actually cried during our last lecture including me and I would take all of his courses if i could. hes literally the best person ever and the best prof, highly recommend!

Dr. Peker is one of the few professors who genuinely still cares about his student's well-being. Dr. Peker replied to emails almost instantaneously and offered any kind of support he could. He is a remarkable professor.

Amazing Professor. Cares highly for his students and is always available to answer any questions with pleasure. I would easily choose professor Peker for another class if I had the chance. If you have the opportunity to take a course with him, do it!
Excellent professor. Very organized and goes above and beyond to clearly explain concepts.

I believe everyone thinks he's the best prof :) The professor respects his students and gives pretty clear instructions on what he wants us to learn. Grading is very loose and very accessible outside the class. Best professor ever seen
Literally the sweetest. Always available to help out and very understanding. He has a good sense of humor and he isn't boring! Great prof, we need more professors like him.
Il est EXCELLENT!! si tu hésites a prendre le cours, je te rassure prend le tu ne vas pas le regretter!!!

Professor Peker was one of my favourite profs so far. His assignments are very straight forward, and his exams are mostly multiple choice which are very fair. He is accessible outside of class and answers e-mails very fast. Although attendance was mandatory, he was extremely understanding if you e-mailed him that you were unable to show! :)

I have problems with depression and anxiety. Attendance is worth a lot and I was always refused psychiatric notes from other professors so I stopped asking in general. However, other students in class told me he was lenient and accepted if one could not come to class. I would've asked if I knew Prof. Peker was so understanding.

Prof. Efe is an amazing and fair professor. He is very approachable and replies to his emails quickly (keep in mind this course had to be taken online due to COVID). He definitely is passionate and knowledgeable in what he teaches which makes the subject of the course much more entertaining!

Dr. Peker is really an amazing teacher, you can really tell he cares about his students and their success. The class consisted of one small paper, one midterm, one group project, and a final. Because this was an online class a ten percent was given you participated in the discussion threads. I would definitely take him again.

He is literally the best prof I've had so far. The assignments are very straight forward and the outline is created for you (just fill in the blanks). He is very considerate of your time and your thoughts, very simple material.
Efe is a young professor who's still finding his feet in the world of teaching who's fair in his method of teaching and is extremely approachable in class. Highly recommend!

Meh. Spends too much time talking about current issues irrelevant to course topics and does group projects. Tests seem to come from a test bank and not what he actually teachers (asked if there were stats, said no, but there was). But he's caring, friendly, reachable and wants students to succeed :)

I really have enjoyed having him as my prof! He is such a nice guy and really funny too. He marks attendance though and every class you miss is 1% off up to a max. of 10% (hes understands so email him). Even though I didn't expect as much history, he makes this class interesting and you can see how passionate he is. Assignments are really fair too.
Literally the best professor. The class requires a lot of reading, but his class is very fun and easy to follow.
He really is the best professor at the university
Loved this class with him. A lot of reading and lecture heavy but I was in his 7-10 class. Cares about students succeeding in his class!

I found this class very informative and enjoyable. He connects the text to real life effectively and encourages people to participate and share their own opinions/experiences. This was his first year at UOttawa- I hope he stays to teach more scs courses.
